{
  "stem": "7506.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It always-- that's always stuck in my mind as-- in today's world-- as that being so strange, that people would have cut bread that way.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But that was certainly the way that always stood out in my mind.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES] And we'd be-- you know, we'd play after the kiddish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we'd eat.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You know, children, us children would play while the parents sat and talked about whatever [PAUSES] was being spoken about those days, which I'm not aware of of that time.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother-- my mother had the candles at home, but when we had the kiddish, we were normally by my grandparents, who had the candles lit.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I attended what is in English called, I suppose, primary school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Dutch, it would be called kleuterskool.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I attended that, which was an ordinary school, a government school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I also went to Jewish school for [NON-ENGLISH], which was just Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "More so when we had moved to one of the newer suburb of Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There I had a good friend, a non-Jewish friend, who-- with whom I went to school when I had moved to a different school, a higher-grade school.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But in the early years, I didn't have any non-Jewish friends.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because of the part that we lived in Amsterdam, on that canal, there was a whole new area built.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And [PAUSES] although I don't know the exact reasons, I would assume [PAUSES] that my parents wanted to be in a newer area with more modern housing and newer schools.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was approximately-- [PAUSES] I would say I was approximately 10 years old. 9 or 10.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Obviously, although I'm speaking English, all my previous life has been in Dutch.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
